//Write a C program to add between two numbers using function with pointers.
1. Start.
2. Prompt the user for two integers.
3. Read the integers from user input.
4. Pass the addresses of the integers to the addNumbers function.
5. The function will calculate the sum of the two integers.
6. The result will be stored in a variable pointed to by the third pointer.
7. Print the result, displaying the two input integers and their sum.
8. End.
